{{Infobox artwork | title = Alone in the World | image_file = Bouguereau Seule-au-monde.jpg | caption = ''Alone in the World'' (c.1867) | painting_alignment = | image_size = 220px | alt = | other_language_1 = French | other_title_1 = Seule au Monde | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[William-Adolphe Bouguereau]] | year = {{start date|c.1867}} | medium = [[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | material = | subject = | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | height_imperial = | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter_metric = | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | condition = | city = | museum = | coordinates = | owner = | url = }} '''''Alone in the World''''' ({{lang-fr|Seule au Monde}}) is a painting created by nineteenth-century French artist [[William-Adolphe Bouguereau]]. Although the exact year of creation is unknown, [[Theo van Gogh (art dealer)|Theo van Gogh]] acquired it in 1867 so it may be placed in the early part of Bouguereau's career.<ref name="wissman">{{cite book|last=Wissman |first=Fronia E. |title=Bouguereau |publisher=Pomegranate Artbooks |location=San Francisco |date=1996 |page= |isbn=978-0876545829}}</ref>
The painting depicts a peasant girl holding a [[violin]] and standing on a bridge over the [[Seine]] in Paris. She is looking to her left with a melancholy expression. The cathedral of [[Notre Dame de Paris|Notre Dame]] can be seen in the background, as well as a bridge which appears to be the [[Pont Royal]]. This indicates that the girl is standing on the [[Pont de Solférino]].
